The Filing Is the Protest

âš–ï¸ Core Message

Filing turns grievance into action. Speech becomes record; record becomes remedy.
ğŸ“– Lesson Content

1. Courts remember dockets, not conversations. Paper = presence.
2. Pick the right vehicle: Motion, Notice, Application, or Complaint.
3. Align the ask with the rule â€” every request should cite an authority.
4. Write numbered facts; attach proof; end with a proposed order when appropriate.
ğŸ“ Assignment

Draft a oneâ€‘page 'Notice of Record Preservation' converting a key event into numbered facts with a short ask.
âœ… Model Response

UNITED STATES DISTRICT COURT

DISTRICT OF ARIZONA

 

CHARLES MAYRON, Plaintiff,

v.

JENNIFER RYAN-TOUHILL, in her official capacity, et al., Defendants.

 

Case No. 2:25-cv-02480-SHD

 

NOTICE OF RECORD PRESERVATION

 

1. Plaintiff submits this Notice to preserve the record concerning [event] on [date].

2. Supporting proof is attached as Exhibit A (tracking/email).

3. Plaintiff requests the Court take notice of this preservation for all subsequent proceedings.

 

CERTIFICATE OF SERVICE

 

I certify that on August 18, 2025, I mailed a true and correct copy of this

Notice to the Office of the Arizona Attorney General, 2005 N Central Ave,

Phoenix, AZ 85004.

 

/s/ Charles Mayron

 

